"NEWS GOV-MO: The University of Macau awarded honorary doctoral degrees to seven outstanding individuals.
The "2021 Honorary Degree and Higher Degree Award Ceremony" was held today (11th). Liu Zunyi, Chen Kaixian, Nakamura Shuji, Li Lanjuan, Li Xiaoliang, Zhu Lilan, and Jiang Chaohui were awarded the University of Macau's honorary doctoral degrees in recognition of their outstanding achievements and significant contributions to society and education.
During the ceremony, the Chief Executive and Macau University Supervisor, Secretary for Social Affairs and Culture, Ouyang Yu, accompanied by Macau University Council Chairman, Lin Jincheng, and President of Macau University, Song Yonghua, presented the honorary doctoral degrees.
Professor Liu Zunyi was awarded the honorary degree of Doctor of Education, Professor Chen Kaixian was awarded the honorary degree of Doctor of Science, Professor Nakamura Shuji was awarded the honorary degree of Doctor of Science, Professor Li Lanjuan was awarded the honorary degree of Doctor of Science, Professor Li Xiaoliang was awarded the honorary degree of Doctor of Business Administration, Professor Zhu Lilan was awarded the honorary degree of Doctor of Science, and Ms. Jiang Chaohui was awarded the honorary degree of Doctor of Science.
In his speech, Ouyang Yu first expressed warm congratulations and high respect to the seven outstanding individuals who were awarded the honorary doctoral degrees. They have made extraordinary achievements in different fields and made outstanding contributions to the development of the country and progress of the world. At the same time, Ouyang also expressed his sincerest wishes to the graduates and parents, and sincere respect to the university's dedicated and academically excellent teaching staff."
At the lecture of the School of Humanities at the University of Melbourne, Professor Sun Yifeng read Professor Liu Zunyi's eulogy and expressed that Professor Liu is a renowned economist globally, known for his exceptional academic achievements and forward-thinking educational philosophy.
In addition to his achievements in economic development, economic growth, and East Asian economy, he is also a visionary educational leader.
In short, he has made outstanding contributions in many fields.
Professor Sun Yifeng, while reading Professor Nakamura Shuji's eulogy, stated that Professor Nakamura is a pioneer in sustainable energy technology.
He became one of the three winners of the 2014 Nobel Prize in Physics for inventing the blue LED (light-emitting diode).

Professor Sun Yifeng, while reading Professor Li Lanjuan's commendation, stated that Professor Li Lanjuan is the pioneer of the artificial liver industry in China. She created the unique and effective Li's artificial liver system, which has made major breakthroughs in the treatment of severe liver disease and cirrhosis, significantly reducing the mortality rate of liver cirrhosis.
In the fight against the COVID-19 pandemic, her and her team's "four-against-two balance" program and the three technologies of artificial liver, microbiome and stem cells significantly improved the survival rate of critically ill patients.
Professor Sun Yifeng, while reading Professor Li Xiaoliang's commendation, stated that Professor Li Xiaoliang laid the foundation for innovation in operations management and shaped the thinking of supply chain theory and practice. He thoroughly changed the business models all over the world.
Professor Li Xiaoliang is famous for popularizing the concept of the "long whip effect" in operations management, and exploring measures to address this phenomenon.
Nowadays, with the pandemic and the tense economic situation in various countries, the bullwhip effect is becoming more prominent, causing serious damage to the supply chain.
Li Xiaoliang's far-sighted research is like sending charcoal in the snow, helping the industry to cope with the predicament, thereby bringing huge social value.
Sun Yifeng read Zhu Lilan's compliments and stated that in her research work, she discovered a breakthrough and innovative staining technique for preparing samples, which has a high reputation among domestic and foreign peers in the scientific community.
She was honored with important titles such as the international Eurasian Academy of Sciences, and she has won a deservedly high position in the world's technological temple with her brilliant achievements.
Chen Xin, the acting dean of the Australia-China Institute of Medicine and Research, read Chen Kaixian's compliments and stated that Professor Chen Kaixian has been engaged in drug research and development for over 40 years, and his outstanding scientific achievements and important contributions to the country, Macau, Macau University, and National Key Laboratory have earned him a high international position and reputation.
His active promotion of the development of traditional Chinese medicine in Macau and the Greater Bay Area fully embodies his sense of mission to contribute to the national development strategy of medicine.
The president of the University of Macau, Technology and Science, Xu Chengzhong, read a speech in praise of Jiang Chaohui, saying that Ms. Jiang's major inventions and patents in research and development, which now total more than 15 items related to storage virtualization, navigation, file systems, and power management, are all highly practical and widely used, improving the convenience of human life.
As a distinguished inventor, Ms. Jiang is often able to simplify complex science and technology and popularize it for the general public.
Finally, Chen Kai, as a representative of Honorary Doctor, read the speech of thanks.
He was happy to see that the medical industry in Macau and the Greater Bay Area has set a good example: from the first traditional Chinese medicine quality research national key laboratory established by the University of Macau to the vigorous development of traditional Chinese medicine in the Greater Bay Area, the University of Macau has made a huge contribution by integrating excellent talents in the field of traditional Chinese medicine in the Greater Bay Area.
In addition, he believes that the management team at the University of Macau has a far-sighted vision and provides a research-friendly environment for students not only academically, but also contributes to society by producing many responsible and talented individuals.
He is honored to have the opportunity to exchange and cooperate with the University of Macau, and he sincerely congratulates the recent achievements of the university.